  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3690711"> </a><h4 class="pHead4" >
Errors
</h4>    

<a name="wp3690712"> </a><p class="pBody" >
The parameters <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">min</span> and <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">max</span> must be specified such that <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">min</span> is less than or equal to <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">max</span>. Otherwise, the assertion fails on each tested clock cycle for which <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> changed from <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">max</span>.
</p>    
<a name="wp3690713"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Notes
</h3>    

<a name="wp3690714"> </a><p class="pNumber" >
 1.	The assertion check compares the current value of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> with its previous value. Therefore, checking does not start until the second rising clock edge of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">clk</span> after <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">reset_n</span> deasserts.
</p>    
<a name="wp3690715"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
See also
</h3>    

<p class="pCodeShiftTop"></p><a name="wp3690716"> </a><pre class="pCode2" >assert_delta, assert_fifo_index, assert_decrement, assert_no_overflow
</pre>    
